âœ… *HTML5 Basics + Real Interview Questions & Answers* ğŸŒğŸ“‹

*1ï¸âƒ£ Q: What is HTML and why is it important?*
_A:_ HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard markup language used to create the structure of web pages. It organizes content into headings, paragraphs, links, lists, forms, etc.

*2ï¸âƒ£ Q: Whatâ€™s the difference between `<div>` and `<section>`?*
_A:_ `<div>` is a generic container with no semantic meaning. `<section>` is a semantic tag that groups related content with meaning, useful for SEO and accessibility.

*3ï¸âƒ£ Q: What is the difference between `<id>` and `<class>` in HTML?*
_A:_
- `id` is unique for one element
- `class` can be reused on multiple elements
â†’ `id` is used for specific targeting, `class` for grouping styles.

*4ï¸âƒ£ Q: What are semantic tags? Name a few.*
_A:_ Semantic tags clearly describe their purpose. Examples:
`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`, `<footer>`

*5ï¸âƒ£ Q: What is the difference between `<ul>`, `<ol>`, and `<dl>`?*
_A:_
- `<ul>` = unordered list (bullets)
- `<ol>` = ordered list (numbers)
- `<dl>` = description list (term-definition pairs)

*6ï¸âƒ£ Q: How does a form work in HTML?*
_A:_ Forms collect user input using `<input>`, `<textarea>`, `<select>`, etc. Data is sent using the `action` and `method` attributes to a server for processing.

*7ï¸âƒ£ Q: What is the purpose of the `alt` attribute in an image tag?*
_A:_ It provides alternative text if the image doesnâ€™t load and improves accessibility for screen readers.

